close_reason: Fixed Ollama auto-default model selection so health does not pick unavailable embedding models
body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/455\n\n## Problem\n`pm health` auto-detected Ollama embeddings and selected qwen3-embedding:0.6b without checking it is installed, then attempted a vector refresh that failed (Embedding request failed 404). Health exits ok but emits a noisy, hard-to-action refresh warning.\n\n## Proposed fix\nAuto-detection must only select an INSTALLED embedding model (query ollama tags), otherwise skip vector refresh with a clear remediation (ollama pull <model> / pm config set search keys); health output states which model was chosen and why.\n\n## Definition of done\nHealth never attempts refresh with an unavailable model; remediation hint names the exact pull/config command; spec covers missing-model path with mocked provider."
